{"author":{"id":"5e53c9bce7eeb69e347743575f6133426338c29498e200aa8bf1bef46209d02a"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1680029550,"nonce":"VEyUJf7EShsNY4oNU4UbKRMnxBQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s5YqJH9","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5163#issuecomment-1487442429"},"message":"This could occur only on .org because of being run in a container. `/usr/local/bin/mother/names.dat` would be a container path. I'm not sure if [this is related](https://forum.mothur.org/t/creating-names-and-groups-files/93) but it seems to indicate that those files should be generated - on other infrastructure such as .eu it may successfully write to the conda dir (which is bad, but would work), but inside the container it fails.","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1680037800,"nonce":"Im4XI1mdRCtkut1Y/fEo+A0+W5w=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOAW4Y0s5YqJH9zi80wRM"},"target":"0be4f07d018ca51c803c3fcf626dafb19f2ce11f2c0e405cf01a8878904ac2ae","message":"This could occur only on .org because of being run in a container. `/usr/local/bin/mothur/names.dat` would be a container path. I'm not sure if [this is related](https://forum.mothur.org/t/creating-names-and-groups-files/93) but it seems to indicate that those files should be generated - on other infrastructure such as .eu it may successfully write to the conda dir (which is bad, but would work), but inside the container it fails.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1680037750,"nonce":"hILvFihSZxPe14s6WT8reLG/Crc=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s5YquTb","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5163#issuecomment-1487594715"},"message":"Okay, I should have read a bit more closely - the `/usr/local/bin/mothur/names.dat` path is only a fallback. The actual issue is caused by the `names.dat` symlink pointing to `None`:\n\n```console\n[g2main@galaxy-web-03 49203482]$ ls -lh working/names.dat\nlrwxrwxrwx. 1 g2main G-803372 4 Mar 28 16:01 working/names.dat -\u003e None\n[g2main@galaxy-web-03 49203482]$ grep names.dat tool_script.sh\nset -o pipefail; export TERM=vt100;  ln -s 'None' names.dat \u0026\u0026 ln -s '/corral4/main/objects/a/d/b/dataset_adbdf650-a1a8-4569-86ee-e01f34eccc24.dat' fasta.dat \u0026\u0026  echo 'unique.seqs( name=names.dat, fasta=fasta.dat, format=name )' | sed 's/ //g' | mothur | tee mothur.out.log\n```\n\nHowever, that is indeed the case with the particular bug report history I tried - there is no selectable `mothur.names` or `mothur.count` file in the history. This input is optional, so the tool can still run, but seems not to function correctly in this case.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1680113425,"nonce":"Zh2kcsIbngDjD4McmQg1ykRi0/s=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s5YwXlS","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5163#issuecomment-1489074514"},"message":"usegalaxy.eu is experiencing this now after upgrading to 23.0. The issue is with the handling of the optional `names` input when it is left blank/unspecified. Prior to 23.0, [the conditional in the tool](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/42f32d4c093fc3b8d2604c635e1f862fee695a05/tools/mothur/unique.seqs.xml#L17) that evaluated `names` would return `false` for both branches and neither the `name` or `count` param would be included in the `unique.seqs()` call, which is the correct behavior when `names` is not specified.\n\nIn 23.0, the first branch is evaluating `true` even when the `names` input is unspecified, likely due to the following:\n\n```\ngalaxy.security.object_wrapper WARNING 2023-03-29 13:54:36,344 [pN:main.1,p:201504,tN:WSGI_1] Unable to create dynamic subclass SafeStringWrapper__galaxy.model.none_like.None__NoneType__NotImplementedType__Number__SafeStringWrapper__ToolParameterValueWrapper__bool__bytearray__ellipsis for \u003cclass 'galaxy.model.none_like.NoneDataset'\u003e, None: type() doesn't support MRO entry resolution; use types.new_class()\n```","files":null}]}